Safe Moza HID probe and capture commands

Usage: wheelctl moza [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  init-lane                          Create a Moza R5 validation lane manifest and capture directory
  probe                              Probe connected Moza HID devices without sending FFB writes
  status                             Summarize Moza device and lane readiness without opening HID devices
  descriptor                         Capture descriptor metadata for connected Moza HID devices
  capture-input                      Capture input reports from one Moza HID device without FFB writes
  steering-stream-proof              Record native steering angle samples from the lane R5 endpoint without output writes
  validate-capture                   Validate captured Moza input JSONL through the parser without hardware writes
  analyze-capture                    Analyze raw byte/word movement in a captured Moza input JSONL without hardware writes
  analyze-lane                       Compare required passive lane captures against idle without hardware writes
  sync-role-status                   Sync manifest logical-control semantic_status fields from stored captures
  validate-captures                  Validate every required Moza lane capture through the parser without hardware writes
  pre-output-readiness               Summarize whether a Moza lane is ready for zero-torque or FFB output
  promote-fixture                    Promote a validated Moza capture JSONL into a parser fixture file
  promote-fixtures                   Promote every required Moza lane capture into parser fixture files
  zero                               Send bounded zero-torque output reports to a Moza wheelbase
  watchdog-proof                     Inject a watchdog timeout and prove the response is final zero
  disconnect-proof                   Write zero torque until a disconnect is observed, then attempt final zero
  init                               Run the staged Moza wheelbase handshake in off or standard mode
  torque-test                        Send a gated low-torque ladder after a passing real zero-torque proof
  actuator-profile-smoke             Run a native bounded PIDFF actuator profile after steering feedback is proven
  actuator-visible-smoke             Run a bounded native actuator smoke that must prove visible steering motion
  controlled-angle-smoke             Preflight or run one authorized feedback-bounded native controlled-angle attempt
  authorize-visible-output           Authorize one exact native visible-motion retry after fresh bench-clear
  authorize-controlled-angle-output  Authorize one exact native controlled-angle hardware attempt after fresh bench-clear
  receipt-template                   Write a non-claiming starter receipt for manual Pit House or simulator evidence
  pit-house-observation              Write an observed Pit House UI/process state receipt
  pit-house-evidence                 Capture a no-output Pit House process/window snapshot evidence artifact
  pit-house-availability             Capture a non-claiming Pit House install/process availability receipt
  pit-house-case                     Build one Pit House coexistence case artifact from source receipts
  pit-house-proof                    Build a Pit House coexistence receipt from observed case artifact files
  simulator-telemetry-proof          Build a telemetry-only simulator proof receipt from normalized snapshots
  simulator-ffb-smoke                Build a bounded simulator-to-Moza FFB smoke proof from output logs
  promote-manifest                   Promote manifest completion state only after a live bundle verification passes
  verify-bundle                      Verify a Moza hardware lane receipt bundle before claiming readiness
  audit-lane                         Audit stored verification and manifest-promotion receipts after promotion
  help                               Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --json        Output in JSON format for machine parsing
  -v, --verbose...  Verbose logging
  -h, --help        Print help
